{"id":"2011.14591","submitter":"Sudeshna Basu","authors":"Sudeshna Basu, Susmita Seal","title":"Stability Results Of Small Diameter Properties In Banach Spaces","comments":"3 figures, 20 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.FA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The geometric notion of huskability initiated and developed in [B3], [BR]\n,[EW], [GM] was subsequently extensively studied in the context of dentability\nand Radon Nikodym Property in [GGMS]. In this work, we introduce a new\ngeometric property of Banach space, the Ball Huskable Property ($BHP$), namely,\nthe unit ball has relatively weakly open subsets of arbitrarily small diameter.\nWe compare this property to two related geometric properties, $BSCSP$ namely,\nthe unit ball has convex combination of slices of arbitrarily small diameter\nand $BDP$ namely, the closed unit ball has slices of arbitrarily small\ndiameter. We show $BDP$ implies $BHP$ which in turn implies $BSCSP$ and none of\nthe implications can be reversed. We prove similar results for the\n$w^*$-versions. We prove that all these properties are stable under $l_p$ sum\nfor $1\\leq p \\leq \\infty$. These stability results lead to a discussion in the\ncontext of ideals of Banach spaces. We prove that $BSCSP$ (respectively $BHP$,\n$BDP$) can be lifted from an M-Ideal to the whole space. We also show similar\nresults for strict ideals. We note that the space $C(K,X)^*$ has $w^*$-$BSCSP$\n(respectively $w^*$-$BHP$, $w^*$-$BDP$) when K is dispersed and $X^*$has the\n$w^*$-$BSCSP$ (respectivley $w^*$-$BHP$, $w^*$-$BDP$).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Nov 2020 07:19:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 15 Jan 2021 17:32:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 4 Aug 2021 20:49:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-06"}
