{"id":"2012.00563","submitter":"Yinchuan Li","authors":"Yinchuan Li, Xiaodong Wang, Robert L. Olesen","title":"Unfolded Deep Neural Network (UDNN) for High Mobility Channel Estimation","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.IT math.IT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  High mobility channel estimation is crucial for beyond 5G (B5G) or 6G\nwireless communication networks. This paper is concerned with channel\nestimation of high mobility OFDM communication systems. First, a\ntwo-dimensional compressed sensing problem is formulated by approximately\nlinearizing the channel as a product of an overcomplete dictionary with a\nsparse vector, in which the Doppler effect caused by the high mobility channel\nis considered. To solve the problem that the traditional compressed sensing\nalgorithms have too many iterations and are time consuming, we propose an\nunfolded deep neural network (UDNN) as the fast solver, which is inspired by\nthe structure of iterative shrinkage-thresholding algorithm (ISTA). All the\nparameters in UDNN (e.g. nonlinear transforms, shrinkage thresholds,\nmeasurement matrices, etc.) are learned end-to-end, rather than being\nhand-crafted. Experiments demonstrate that the proposed UDNN performs better\nthan ISTA for OFDM high mobility channel estimation, while maintaining\nextremely fast computational speed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Nov 2020 15:21:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-02"}
